FT  13 MAY 91 / Observer: Hear Hear
'At the beginning of my review, I stated that 1990 had been a difficult
year. For me, it was also a rewarding one.'
So says Mick Newmarch, chief executive of Prudential Corporation, writing in
his annual report for 1990 - a year in which, it may be recalled, the Pru's
pre-tax profits rose 9 per cent and his salary rose 43 per cent.
